thread.title: Sanford airport reveals finalists for new CEO

author: Megan Ribbens
title: Sanford airport reveals finalists for new CEO
text:
Sanford airport reveals finalists for new CEO Jul 24, 2015, 6:45am EDT Industries & Tags Megan Ribbens Web Producer Orlando Business Journal Megan Ribbens Web Producer Orlando Business Journal Home of the Day Jim Carchidi Sanford Airport Authority President and CEO Larry Dale will retire Sept. 30. A search committee has narrowed it down to the final four candidates to replace Sanford Airport Authority President and CEO Larry Dale . Dale announced in March his plans to retire Sept. 30 after 14 years at the helm. The four candidates the committee will recommend to the Sanford Airport Authority board of directors include: Tommy Bibb , director of properties at Metropolitan Nashville Airport Authority Diane Crews , vice president of finance and administration for the Sanford Airport Authority Sunil Harman , director of airports at Okaloosa County Robert W. Kennedy , vice president of Montreal, Canada-based Aviation Strategies International
